title: Laura Ingraham US Talk Radio July 28 2016.mp3
description:
Laura Ingraham Podcast July 28, 2016
Conservative talk radio America 

Warren: 'I wish Donald Trump would just disappear'
Elizabeth Warren takes no pleasure in sparring with Donald Trump, she said during a Wednesday night appearance on MSNBC. "Am I right to perceive that you enjoy fighting with Donald Trump?" anchor Rachel Maddow asked the Massachusetts senator.

There has never been a man or a woman, not me, not Bill, nobody more qualified than Hillary Clinton to serve as President of the United States of America.
- Pres. Obama at the Democratic National Convention, July 28, 2016

Juan Williams reacts to the Clinton Foundation investigation and DNC Day 2.

Gov. Pence: 'Against TPP; Trade Should Work for the American People First' Craig Shirley: 'Obama Is Not the Go -To Person On Conservatism; Only Cites Reagan When It's Convenient For His Agenda'

French media to stop publishing photos and names of terrorists
Several French news organisations have said they will no longer publish photographs of people responsible for terrorist killings, to avoid bestowing "posthumous glorification".

The Democrats' well-deserved WikiLeaks blowback
Marc A. Thiessen - Washington Post
Over at the CIA and the National Security Agency headquarters, they must be really enjoying watching Democrats in Philadelphia squirm over WikiLeaks's exposure of tens of thousands of internal Democratic Party emails.

Governor Mike Pence - Republican Party nominee for Vice President.
Craig Shirley - Reagan biographer and New York Times bestselling author.
Dinesh D'Souza - Creator of Hillary's America, in theaters now.

Donald Trump Just Got Hillary Clinton To Admit Her E-mails Are A 'National Security Issue'
Sean Davis - The Federalist
After taunting Hillary Clinton by asking Russian hackers to release 30,000 e-mails she deleted, Donald Trump finally forced Clinton's campaign to admit that her unsanctioned e-mail server scheme was a "national security issue."

The Democrats' well-deserved WikiLeaks blowback
Marc A. Thiessen - Washington Post
Over at the CIA and the National Security Agency headquarters, they must be really enjoying watching Democrats in Philadelphia squirm over WikiLeaks's exposure of tens of thousands of internal Democratic Party emails.

ISIS Terrorist priest killers Adel Kermiche and Abdel Malik pledge loyalty to terror group in sick video
The footage emerged as Kermiche, 19, was exposed as a philanderer who married four times just to have sex - then dumped all his partners within a few days. It was also revealed the fanatics held two nuns as human shields after slitting 85-year-old priest Jacques Hamel's throat in a Catholic church in France.
